# P12-001: Remote / VFS `.pgen` reads (S3, HTTP, any DuckDB filesystem)

Let `read_pfile` / `read_pgen` open a `.pgen` over a DuckDB filesystem (`s3://`,
`https://`, `hf://`, gcs, azure, …), not just local disk — with **targeted region
queries reading only the bytes they need** over the network. That last part is an
architectural edge plink2 does **not** have (see P-context below): this is
ahead-of-upstream work, not parity work. The bar is therefore "does a spike prove
the edge is real," not "does it work at all."

